                <div class="accordion-header">
                  <h3>What documents do I need for international shipping?</h3>
                  <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>For international shipments, you'll need a commercial invoice, a packing list, and a customs declaration form. Depending on the destination country and the contents, you might also need certificates of origin, permits, or licenses. Our system will guide you through the required documentation during the shipping process.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header">
                  <h3>How long does international shipping take?</h3>
                  <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>International shipping times vary depending on the destination, service level, and customs processing. Economy international shipping typically takes 7-10 business days, standard shipping takes 3-5 business days, and express international shipping takes 1-2 business days. Customs clearance can add additional time.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header">
                  <h3>Are there any prohibited items for international shipping?</h3>
                  <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>Yes, prohibited items vary by country but generally include perishable foods, hazardous materials, firearms, alcohol, certain medications, and currency. Each country has specific import restrictions, so we recommend checking the destination country's customs website or contacting our customer service for guidance.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header">
                  <h3>Who pays import duties and taxes?</h3>
                  <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>Import duties and taxes are typically paid by the recipient unless you choose our Delivered Duty Paid (DDP) service, where you pay these fees upfront. The amount varies based on the item value, type, and destination country's regulations. Our shipping calculator can provide estimates of potential duties and taxes.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-panel" id="pricing-panel">
            <div class="accordion">
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header">
                  <h3>How is shipping cost calculated?</h3>
                  <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>Shipping costs are calculated based on package weight, dimensions, origin, destination, service level, and any additional services selected. For accurate pricing, use our shipping calculator or create a shipment in your account to see real-time rates.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="accordion-item">
                <div class="accordion-header">
                  <h3>Do you offer shipping insurance?</h3>
                  <span class="accordion-icon"><i class="fas fa-plus"></i></span>
                </div>
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>Yes, we offer shipping insurance for all packages. Basic coverage is included with most shipping services, and additional coverage can be purchased based on the declared value of your items. Insurance covers loss, damage, and theft during transit.</p>
